<HEADLINE>
<P>
IN DODGERS' WORLD, THERE'S ALWAYS A REASON 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Let's see if I understand this: 
</P>
<P>
 1. Montreal is Lasorda's least favorite stadium. 
</P>
<P>
 2. The indoors of the Astrodome is always a problem. 
</P>
<P>
 3. San Diego is always up and tough on the Dodgers. 
</P>
<P>
 4. Candlestick is a weird place and the Giants are always up. 
</P>
<P>
 5. Atlanta is a championship team and a real problem. 
</P>
<P>
 6. Wrigley Field is cozy and the Cubs tend to hit it out. 
</P>
<P>
 7. The rest of the places have hot, humid weather. 
</P>
<P>
 RICHARD W. TOLBERT 
</P>
<P>
 Anaheim 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Too bad about the impending baseball strike. It will deprive me and all other 
Dodger fans of a late-September race between the Dodgers and Padres to 
determine who is the worst team in the Western Division. 
</P>
<P>
 HERBERT M. SCHOENBERG 
