<HEADLINE>
<P>
AT LEAST, THEY WOULD HAVE GONE WITH A BANG 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 With most of the recent astronomy news devoted to the Apollo 11 anniversary, 
many overlooked the unfortunate fact that the Shoemaker-Levy comet, which had 
traveled billions and billions of miles, took one final dip in trajectory 
before colliding -- barely missing Clipper headquarters. 
</P>
<P>
 SABASTIAN DAHBOUR 
</P>
<P>
 Newport Beach 
