<HEADLINE>
<P>
BASEBALL / DAILY REPORT; DODGERS; TEAM PREPARES FOR STRIKE REFUNDS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DAN HAFNER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Dodgers have set up a ticket-refund policy if there is a strike. Debra 
Duncan, director of ticket operations, said she will send a letter next week to 
season ticket-holders explaining their options.Even if they choose refunds, 
none will be sent out until after games are actually canceled. 
</P>
<P>
 "We hope all games will be played," Duncan said. "But if some are canceled, 
our fans will be taken care of." 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Tonight's game will start at 7:30, preceded by the old-timers' game at 5:45. 
Among those scheduled to play are Tom Lasorda, Don Newcombe, Tommy John, Ron 
Cey, Willie and Tommy Davis, Steve Garvey, Jerry Reuss and Lou Johnson. . . . 
The Astros put Sid Bream on the 15-day disabled list and recalled infielder 
Roberto Petagine from their Tucson triple-A club. Bream suffered a muscle 
strain in his back. DAN HAFNER 
</P>
