<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY NEWSWATCH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Jerry Hick; April Jackson, ; Michael Granberry 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 CHICKEN MUSICK: You may not see many chickens from the freeway, but Orange 
County's tiny egg production has actually shown some growth lately. . . . Not 
that there are many chicken farms left. The only one of any size is Singing Hen 
Chicken Ranch in Cypress -- and it's down to fewer than 100 hens. Actually, 99% 
of all the commercial eggs in the county come from the jail system's James A. 
Musick Branch Jail. Says Cal Meekhof, owner of the Cypress ranch, which once 
had 40,000 birds: "Chicken ranches don't fit in with suburbs." 
</P>
<P>
 LOOK, BUT RESPECT: Since Nicole Brown Simpson's burial at Ascension Cemetery 
in Lake Forest six weeks ago, her unmarked grave has brought a small stream of 
daily visitors. . . . Some leave flowers or even notes, says Thomas R. Flynn, 
director of cemeteries for the local Roman Catholic diocese. "All are welcome, 
but it is a religious cemetery, and we expect people to act in the appropriate 
manner. So far, everyone has." 
</P>
<P>
 PEDAL THE DAY AWAY: How long would it take you to cross America by bicycle if 
you could somehow pedal 24 hours a day? Just under seven days, say riders in 
the annual, corporate-sponsored Race Across America, which starts Sunday at the 
Holiday Inn in Irvine. . . . Four team members split the clock with six hour 
daily shifts each, the others sleeping in support vehicles. Last year's 
winners, from Cypress-based PacifiCare, are back again. They should reach the 
finish line next Saturday in Savannah, Ga. 
</P>
<P>
 REALISTIC SWEAT: Frank Pangborn suggests if you want to go to Hollywood, try 
Irvine Valley College in Irvine first. The actor teaches a seminar there today 
on how to break into acting. Casting director Kathy Smith, who got Pangborn his 
first commercial, will be there to help. Says Pangborn: "It's an extremely 
competitive business. But if you enjoy it, and are willing to sacrifice -- and 
be a realist -- don't be afraid to go for it." Busy Hens 
</P>
<P>
 County egg production reached a five-year high last year. Yield, in dozens: 
</P>
<P>
 1993: 150,939 
</P>
<P>
 Source: Orange County agriculture commissioner 
</P>
