<P>
METROPOLITAN DIGEST / LOS ANGELES COUNTY NEWS IN BRIEF: SOUTH BAY; POLICE 
ARREST SUSPECT IN 12 TICKLISH BURGLARIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A quirky cat burglar who occasionally tickled the feet of residents as they 
slept was arrested recently after Redondo Beach police observed him stealing a 
bicycle from a yard, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 Arnold Collins Jr., 20, of Redondo Beach is suspected of burglarizing 12 homes 
in Redondo Beach and Lawndale since April, Police Sgt. Rick Petersen said. 
</P>
<P>
 The cat burglar would enter homes through unlocked windows and occasionally 
pilfer purses, leaving them in nearby yards after removing cash, Petersen said. 
</P>
<P>
 Police said they began to suspect Collins of the burglaries after observing 
him in the area late at night. 
</P>
<P>
 Undercover police observed Collins peering through windows and walking through 
yards before taking a bicycle from a yard Wednesday near the 2700 block of 
Rockefeller Lane, police said. They arrested him about 2:30 a.m. after he fled 
to a roof. 
</P>
<P>
 Police said they found evidence in Collins' home that linked him to several 
recent burglaries in Redondo Beach. Collins, who allegedly admitted several of 
the burglaries, is being held on $30,000 bail, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 During four of the burglaries, residents awoke after they were tickled, saw 
the suspect and called police. In each case, the suspect fled, Petersen said. 
</P>
