<HEADLINE>
<P>
EAST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: NEWBURY PARK; WOMAN ARRESTED ON MOLESTATION CHARGE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JULIE FIELDS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 45-year-old Newbury Park woman has been arrested on suspicion of molesting a 
14-year-old boy after hiring him to help her move and then showing him nude 
images of herself, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 Laurie Ann Arden was arrested Wednesday after sheriff's deputies learned she 
was living at the E-Z 8 Motel in Newbury Park, said Sheriff's Detective Mike 
Powers. 
</P>
<P>
 Lt. Bill Montijo said several videotapes, computer disks and other computer 
equipment were confiscated in Arden's room. 
</P>
<P>
 Powers said Arden is unemployed, but apparently posed for sexually explicit 
films and magazines as recently as a several months ago. 
</P>
<P>
 "It would appear that they were at least statewide publications," he said. 
</P>
<P>
 According to Powers, Arden had sex with the boy twice in April and May after 
she hired him to help her move out of a rented room on White Oak Lane in 
Newbury Park. Arden allegedly showed him nude images of herself on a computer 
screen and in a magazine, then suggested they have sex. 
</P>
<P>
 Sheriff's detectives began investigating the case in May after the 14-year-old 
boy's mother became suspicious when Arden called the family's home asking for 
her son. 
</P>
<P>
 The boy admitted to having sex with Arden after being questioned by his 
mother, who then called the Sheriff's Department. 
</P>
<P>
 The boy met Arden through a friend who was referred to Arden by a youth 
employment agency in the Conejo Valley, said Powers, who declined to name the 
agency. 
</P>
<P>
 Montijo urged anyone with information about the case to call the Sheriff's 
Department. JULIE FIELDS 
</P>
</TEXT>
