<HEADLINE>
<P>
EAST VALLEY FOCUS: NORTH HOLLYWOOD; VALLEY PLAZA LIBRARY TO REOPEN MONDAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ED BOND 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Valley Plaza branch of the Los Angeles Public Library, closed for more 
than six months because of earthquake damage, will reopen Monday. 
</P>
<P>
 Repairs to the facility at 12311 Vanowen St. in North Hollywood include new 
ceiling lights, carpeting, interior paint and an increased electrical capacity 
to accommodate modern library technology. 
</P>
<P>
 Library hours be from 12:30 to 8 p.m. Mondays and Tuesdays, 12:30 to 5:30 p.m. 
Wednesdays and Thursdays, and 10 a.m. to 5:30 p.m. Fridays and Saturdays. 
</P>
<P>
 City library branches that remain closed because of earthquake damage are Los 
Feliz, Granada Hills, Woodland Hills and the North Hollywood Regional Library. 
For up-to-date recorded information on the status of branch closures, call 
(213) 228-7104. ED BOND 
</P>
