ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: HUNTINGTON BEACH; 2 INSTRUCTORS RECEIVE COSMETOLOGY HONORS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BILL BILLITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Two cosmetology instructors at Golden West College have been named to the 
California Cosmetology Assn.'s Hall of Fame. 
</P>
<P>
 The instructors, Gary Black and Albert Salmon, both of Lake Elsinore, were 
tapped for the honor at the statewide cosmetology association's recent 65th 
annual convention in Bakersfield. 
</P>
<P>
 The Hall of Fame recognition honored the two men for their professional 
accomplishments as well as their community activities. 
</P>
<P>
 In addition to the Hall of Fame honor, Black was given a Lifetime Achievement 
Award at the convention from the Long Beach Hairdressers Guild. 
</P>
<P>
 Black has taught cosmetology courses at Golden West since 1973, and Salmon has 
taught there since 1971. BILL BILLITER 
