<HEADLINE>
<P>
1 CRITICALLY HURT IN LAGUNA CANYON ROAD CRASH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 27-year-old Costa Mesa man was critically injured Friday when he tried to 
make a U-turn on Laguna Canyon Road and was broadsided by a 1994 Ford Explorer 
behind him in the southbound lane, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 Canh Nguyen, who was driving a 1986 Toyota, was airlifted to Mission Hospital 
Regional Medical Center following the 3:30 p.m. crash, about a mile south of 
the San Diego Freeway, Irvine police Sgt. Craig Smith said. 
</P>
<P>
 Nguyen was in critical condition late Friday with major head injuries. 
</P>
<P>
 Laguna Canyon Road, the scene of numerous traffic deaths in recent years, was 
closed for four hours between El Toro Road and the San Diego Freeway as a 
result of the collision. 
</P>
<P>
 A passenger in the Toyota, 18-year-old Thao Nguyen of Costa Mesa, received 
minor injuries and was treated for back and leg pain at Irvine Medical Center. 
</P>
<P>
 The driver of the Explorer was unhurt. 
</P>
<P>
 Police said that neither alcohol nor excessive speed were factors in the 
crash. For an unknown reason, the Toyota slowed and began to make a U-turn, 
Smith said. The other driver, following several car lengths behind, tried to 
evade the Toyota. 
</P>
</TEXT>
