<HEADLINE>
<P>
14-YEAR-OLD KILLED, 3 HURT IN CRASH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A Palmdale teen-ager was killed and three others were injured when the car in 
which they were riding veered out of control and rolled over, authorities said 
Friday. 
</P>
<P>
 Tiffany Daproza, 14, was pronounced dead at the scene of the accident, which 
occurred at 5:50 p.m. Thursday on Avenue P, just east of 10th Street East. 
</P>
<P>
 The driver of the car, Scott Ibbotson, 20, of Palmdale was arrested on 
suspicion of vehicular manslaughter and reckless driving. On Friday, he 
remained in jail in lieu of $25,000 bail at the Los Angeles County Sheriff's 
Department's Antelope Valley Station. 
</P>
<P>
 Deputies said Ibbotson was driving west in a 1989 Honda Civic, erratically and 
at high speed, when the car went out of control, slid into the dirt shoulder 
and rolled over, ejecting Daproza and Sara Woleslagle, 17, also of Palmdale. 
</P>
<P>
 Woleslagle was reported in good condition Friday at Lancaster Community 
Hospital. 
</P>
<P>
 Her sister, Amy Woleslagle, 15, and Ibbotson, who both remained in the car 
when the accident occurred, were treated at Palmdale Hospital Medical Center 
and released. 
</P>
<P>
 Daproza was a student at Palmdale High School, as are the other two girls. 
</P>
</TEXT>
