<HEADLINE>
<P>
RELIGION NOTES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JOHN DART 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 RELIEF GRANT: Church World Service, the relief arm of the National Council of 
Churches, has given $100,000 to the San Fernando Valley Interfaith Council to 
aid earthquake relief efforts by the Chatsworth-based organization. 
</P>
<P>
 Nearly $21,000 of that money will enable the council to join the KYDS (Keep 
Youth Doing Something) jobs program in the Valley, said Kimberly Hall, director 
of the council's Earthquake Response Project. 
</P>
<P>
 More than $11,000 will provide for a year's lease on a warehouse in the West 
Valley and $10,000 will go toward aiding families who have unmet needs, she 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 About $57,000 of the grant will go toward administrative costs. 
</P>
<P>
 OUTDOOR SHABBAT: As synagogues gear up for open houses and special events to 
attract new members prior to the High Holy Days and religious school fall 
terms, Temple Solael in West Hills is offering outdoor Friday night services 
the next two weeks at Knapp Ranch Park. 
</P>
<P>
 Rabbi Harold Caminker will lead worship services at 7:30 p.m. next week and at 
6 p.m. on Aug. 12, with families invited to eat a picnic dinner beforehand. The 
park is on Kittridge Street. For information, call (818) 348-3885. 
</P>
<P>
 Temple Solael, a Reform synagogue, will hold the first of six formal open 
house receptions at its facility, 6601 Valley Circle Blvd., on Aug. 7 from 11 
a.m. to 2 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
 Before then, however, Temple Beth Torah, a Reform congregation at 16651 
Rinaldi St., Granada Hills, will hold an open house Sunday from 1:30 to 4 p.m. 
For information, call (818) 831-0835. 
</P>
<P>
 ASSYRIAN PASTOR: William Nissan, pastor of the Assyrian Church of Ninevah in 
Panorama City, will speak on his life growing up in the Middle East and coming 
to America in a talk next Saturday at 2 p.m. in the Seventh-day Adventist 
Church, 20550 Roscoe Blvd., Canoga Park. 
</P>
<P>
 Nissan, whose 100-member congregation backed the San Fernando Valley Crusade 
with Luis Palau in June, will relate his talk to the biblical stories about 
Ninevah, whose ancient site is in present-day Iraq. 
</P>
<P>
 Soprano Jeanette Parsadanian will also perform. An offering will be taken. For 
information, call Lynda Keena at (805) 493-4563. 
</P>
<P>
 CLASSICAL CONCERT: Works by Beethhoven, Vivaldi, Bach, Haydn and other master 
composers will be performed in concert at 7 p.m. Sunday at Salem Lutheran 
Church, 1211 N. Brand Blvd., Glendale. 
</P>
<P>
 There will be piano, flute, oboe and trumpet solos. Soprano Cara Clove and 
baritone Paul Munsch will sing. 
</P>
<P>
 An offering will be taken for student scholarships to the national Lutheran 
Summer Music Program. For information, call (818) 243-3193. JOHN DART 
</P>
