THEY HOPE TO LURE CONTRIBUTORS TO RESEARCH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Lure, one of the best grass horses in racing, will be running for research. 
</P>
<P>
 Claiborne Farm and Mrs. William Haggin Perry, Lure's owners, announced Friday 
that 1% of his future earnings will go to the Grayson-Jockey Club Research 
Foundation's recently established Racing for Research Program. 
</P>
<P>
 The 5-year-old Lure is scheduled to run in the Bernard Baruch Handicap on Aug. 
12 at Saratoga. 
