<HEADLINE>
<P>
WEEKEND TV; FOCUS ON 'GENDER WARS,' BASEBALL STRIKE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By N.F. MENDOZA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Anchor Judy Woodruff is the host of Sunday's "Gender Wars" on CNN, which 
explores women's struggle to end unfair sexual discrimination, which has passed 
through the '90s prism and emerged as a source of new excess and abuse, at 9 
p.m. The program repeats at midnight. 
</P>
<P>
 Sunday's "This Week With David Brinkley" on ABC pitches the baseball strike 
deadline and sports salary caps, which are discussed by Donald Fehr, executive 
director of Major League Baseball Players Assn.; Richard Ravitch, president and 
CEO of the Player Relations Committee, and Bud Selig, owner of the Milwaukee 
Brewers and acting baseball commissioner, 11 a.m., Channels 7, 3, 10 and 42. 
N.F. MENDOZA 
